[src:1116-in-ireland/1110-in-ireland] In the time leading up to the Norman invasion of Ireland, the Normans, were invited guests of Irish royalty.
[src:1116-in-ireland/1116-in-ireland] The following is a list of events from the year **1116 in Ireland**.
[src:1116-in-ireland/1116-in-ireland] Ruaidrí Ua Conchobair (Modern Irish: Ruaidhrí Ó Conchobhair, or, Ruairí Ó Conchúir; commonly anglicised as Rory O'Conor) (d.
[src:1116-in-ireland/1116-in-ireland] 1198) was King of Connacht from 1156 to 1186, and High King of Ireland from 1166 to 1183.
[src:1116-in-ireland/1116-in-ireland] He was the last High King of Ireland before the Norman invasion of Ireland (Brian Ua Néill and Edward Bruce both claimed the title with opposition in later years).
